http://www.americanprogress.org/   As tax day approaches and American families prepare to pay their fair share, more and more big corporations are hiding their assets in corporate tax shelters and offshore havens, forcing average taxpayers to make up the difference.  http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/pages/frontline/shows/tax/etc/synopsis.html  PBS's Frontline reports, the General Accounting Office "estimates that illegitimate tax shelters cost the government more than $85 billion in recent years." Corporations are taxed at 35%, but with the help of shelters, large corporations pay less than half of that.  http://www.progressivetrail.org/articles/031209Drutman.shtml  And that means the average American is left holding the bag, paying about 15% more than they should. Last year, for example, "corporate tax revenues fell to only 7.4% of federal tax receipts, the second lowest level on record. (In the 1940s, corporations contributed almost half of federal taxes.)" Read the entire Frontline piece, "Tax Me If You Can." http://www.pbs.org/wgbh/pages/frontline/shows/tax/etc/synopsis.html